.TH "gfs2_link" 9 "gfs2_link" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gfs2_link \- Link to a file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gfs2_link
.BI "(struct dentry *old_dentry "  ","
.BI "struct inode *dir "  ","
.BI "struct dentry *dentry "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "old_dentry" 12
The inode to link
.IP "dir" 12
Add link to this directory
.IP "dentry" 12
The name of the link
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Link the inode in "old_dentry" into the directory "dir" with the
name in "dentry".
.SH "RETURN"
errno
